ria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fgr1665703523770.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgr1665703523770.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgr1665703523770.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fgr1665703523770\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__p_d175733e1_d175734e1_d175735e1\">When you start the Debugger, it attempts to load the configuration file <span class=\"ph filepath\">udbg.cnf</span> containing the Debugger preferences and state. If this file does not exist (which is the case the first time you start the Debugger after installing Uniface), it establishes a default state and preferences for the active Debugger session.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__p_d175736e1_d175737e1_d175738e1\">By default, the Debugger uses the following unnamed states:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__li_d53567e1_d53568e1_d53569e1\">Default state—created by the Debugger at start-up when the <span class=\"ph filepath\">udbg.cnf</span> configuration file is missing.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__li_d53570e1_d53571e1_d53572e1\">Last-used state—active state at the moment state is saved.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__p_d175739e1_d175740e1_d175741e1\">By default, the current state is saved when the Debugger is closed. The current state can be saved as a named state to the Debugger’s internal list of states and saved to the configuration file for repeated use.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgr1665703523770__p_d175742e1_d175743e1_d175744e1\">Debugger preferences allow you to load and save Debugger state information and determine the Debugger form windows to be opened at start-up.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bei1665702859812.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the Uniface Debugger</a><p>You can configure the Uniface Debugger by setting breakpoints and watches, and selecting preferences and settings from the View menu. The Uniface Debugger settings, watches, and breakpoints make up its state, which can be saved to the configuration file for repeated use.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayx1665702860536.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Breakpoints</a><p>A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfi1665703523458.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Watches</a><p>Watches are designated fields, variables, expressions, and functions that are continuously monitored while the application or component is debugged.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527494\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527494\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Debugger State Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The state of the Debugger consists of current settings, watches, and breakpoints. The current state can be saved as a named configuration for repeated use. When you start the Debugger, it attempts to load the configuration file udbg.cnf containing the Debugger preferences and state. If this file does not exist (which is the case the first time you start the Debugger after installing Uniface), it establishes a default state and preferences for the active Debugger session. By default, the Debugger uses the following unnamed states: Default state—created by the Debugger at start-up when the udbg.cnf configuration file is missing. Last-used state—active state at the moment state is saved. By default, the current state is saved when the Debugger is closed. The current state can be saved as a named state to the Debugger’s internal list of states and saved to the configuration file for repeated use. Debugger preferences allow you to load and save Debugger state information and determine the Debugger form windows to be opened at start-up. Related Links Configuring the Uniface Debugger You can configure the Uniface Debugger by setting breakpoints and watches, and selecting preferences and settings from the View menu. The Uniface Debugger settings, watches, and breakpoints make up its state, which can be saved to the configuration file for repeated use. Breakpoints A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. Watches Watches are designated fields, variables, expressions, and functions that are continuously monitored while the application or component is debugged. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}